 Well, I&#39;m not sure if this person is an actual debunker, if its&#39; just a
pe=
rsonal attack. One of the other members of Grass harp, who was also a
membe=
r here, thought she could judge and attack others by the &quot;vibes&quot;
she got fr=
om them. I ripped into this person for being so egotistical
and arrogant, a=
nd IO think this Alice that is attacking now might be
doing so out of reven=
ge. Not being one to back away form an argument, I
kinda keep it going, no =
doubt wrongly.



 Frank



________________________________

From: EVP-I=
TC@yahoogroups.com [mailto:EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com] On Behalf
Of Vicki Talb=
ott
Sent: Friday, August 04, 2006 1:52 PM
To: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com
Subje=
ct: RE: [EVP-ITC] amys back



Hi Frank and Andrea,



I completely agree=
, Andrea.  I think we also need to keep in mind that
certain methods and te=
chnological devices will work for some and not for
others, especially if th=
ere is a &quot;debunker mentality&quot; going on, but even
if there is not.  For exam=
ple, the Spiricom device has not worked very
well for any others who have t=
ried it since its inception; according to
Mark Macy, all they have managed =
to get are very simple EVP, which we
all have gotten from our digital or an=
alog voice recorders.  The Scole
Experiment people have said that debunkers=
 inhibit the interaction, so
why have them around or bother with them?



=
There is also the &quot;medium&quot; theory, which many researchers claim is
necessar=
y to successful communication.  I don&#39;t consider myself a medium
in the cur=
rent sense of the term, but I guess I am in that I receive
some pretty good=
 EVP at times, while others try and try and receive
nothing. 



I don&#39;t g=
et discouraged if I try a method that has worked well for
others, in the pa=
st or currently, and it doesn&#39;t work for me.  After
all, it&#39;s all about our=
 etheric communicators and how they can
communicate with us as individuals.=
  Let the debunkers have their say
and we can continue on with our research=
, right?  Vicki

Andrea Carr &lt;ACARR3@...&gt; wrote:

	Frank I agree abou=
t the debunkers to let it go. Would they even
know if they captured an EVP =
themselves or rationalize it all away? Like
I said I have seen & listened t=
o your box live and heard your guys say
&quot;Purple Princess&quot; directly off the =
box without it being analyzed-this
was not put in a program when I heard it=
 they just came out and said it
clear as day. I knew it was your guys too b=
ecause they have a different
sound to them then when the spirits Chris was =
talking to spoke. IMHO if
the debunkers don&#39;t want to believe they lose out=
 as you&#39;re willing to
share something that was supposed to be made and you =
actually did it & I
don&#39;t care if you got help to make the box-you made it =
and it works!!!!!

	Andrea

	-----Original Message-----
	From: EVP-ITC@yaho=
ogroups.com [mailto:EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com]
On Behalf Of Vicki Talbott
	Se=
nt: Friday, August 04, 2006 1:54 PM
	To: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com
	Subject: =
RE: [EVP-ITC] amys back

	I&#39;d say that would be your best bet at this point=
.

	Sumption Frank &lt;fsumption@...&gt; wrote: 

		Yeah, but this one=
 bitch has made it personal, and I&#39;m
taking up the challenge, but as far as=
 she, maybe I should let it go!?

		 Frank 






